{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2022/07/05/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pandas.pydata.org/\">Pandas</a> - Flexible and powerful data analysis / manipulation library for Python, providing labeled data structures similar to R data.frame objects, statistical functions, and much more.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developers.arcgis.com/python/api-reference/\">ArcGIS Python API</a> - The ArcGIS API for Python is a powerful, modern and easy to use Pythonic library to perform GIS visualization and analysis, spatial data management and GIS system administration tasks that can run both interactively, and using scripts. This library enables easy use of pandas within the ArcGIS platform.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://partridge.readthedocs.io/en/stable/readme.html\">Partridge</a> - Partridge is a Python 3.6+ library for working with GTFS feeds using pandas DataFrames.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://udst.github.io/pandana/\">Pandana</a> - Urban network analysis library intended to help planners compute quick accessibility metrics or shortest paths. Additional Information: License: AGPL-3.0