aps from OpenStreetMap data.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/abdullahselek/HerePy\">HerePy</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/abdullahselek/HerePy\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">76</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":76,\"repo\":\"abdullahselek/HerePy\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A library that provides a Python interface to HERE APIs.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://pysal.org\">PySAL</a> - The Python Spatial Analysis Library is a collection of algorithms for exploring spatial correlations and other spatial relationships.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cityseer.benchmarkurbanism.com/\">city-seer-api</a> - A package for pedestrian-scale network-based urban analysis: network analysis, landuse accessibilities and mixed uses, statistical aggregations.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ggplot2.tidyverse.org/\">ggplot2</a> - Resource for plotting a wide range of data (useful for visualizing survey data). Additional Information: GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Planning Coding Resources</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/r-spatial/leafgl\">leafgl</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/r-spatial/leafgl\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">234</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":234,\"repo\":\"r-spatial/leafgl\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - R package for fast web-gl rendering for leaflet maps.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Geospatial Data and Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://qgis.org/en/site/\">QGIS</a> - This open source GIS suite allows users to create, edit, visualise, analyse and publish geospatial information on Windows, Mac, Linux, BSD and mobile devices.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Geospatial Data and Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://flowmap.blue\">flowmap-blue</a> - Create geographic flow maps representing your data published in Google Sheets. Visualize numbers of movements between locations (origin-destination data).</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Geospatial Data and Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.omnisci.com/\">Omnisci</a> - Geotemporal enabled high performance database capable of doing GPU accelerated queries.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Geospatial Data and Visualization</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/domlysz/BlenderGIS\">BlenderGIS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/domlysz/BlenderGIS\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.7k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":5681,\"repo\":\"domlysz/BlenderGIS\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - BlenderGIS is a free and open-source add on for <a href=\"https://www.blender.org/\">Blender</a> which allows users to explore, query, and visualize data directly through Blender's GUI.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Public Engagement Tools and Platforms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://engage.njtpa.org/\">NJTPA Engage</a> - Database of 300 + public engagement tools, techniques, and software. Searchable on multiple levels.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Public Engagement Tools and Platforms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.socialpinpoint.com/\">Social Pinpoint</a> - Social Pinpoint is a proprietary digital public engagement tool that allows users to give feedback and share their inspirations through interactive maps, surveys, participatory budgeting exercises, and idea wall forums.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Public Engagement Tools and Platforms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.hellolamppost.co.uk/\">Hello Lamp Post</a> - Hello Lamp Post is a proprietary text and SMS-based on-street public engagement tool that uses physical signage and mobile devices to get citizen feedback, improve wayfinding, promote local events and services, or provide creative educational content.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"APA-Technology-Division/urban-and-regional-planning-resources","categoryHTML":"<h2>Platforms and Software Resources</h2><h3>Public Engagement Tools and Platforms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.maptionnaire.com\">Maptionnaire</a> - Provides map-based tools for designing questionnaires, collecting survey data, and conveying information.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-05T23:38:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"catdevnull/awesome-zig","categoryHTML":"<h2>Misc libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/natecraddock/ziglua\">natecraddock/ziglua</a><a data-role=\"trackaw